In England, in the seven days to 15 May, there were 11,832 new confirmed cases (21.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 May, there were 11,497 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 3% (335 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 May is 3,890,081 (6,911.2 cases per 100,000 population).
